# Quick build & production planner

When changing the **+** quick build, multi-input planning, or plan‚Üítree layout:

1. **Read first:** `docs/QUICK_BUILD_AND_PLANNER.md` (full flow, file map, limitations).

2. **Planning logic** ‚Üí `src/lib/productionPlanner.ts`  
   - One machine @ 100% on chosen recipe; recursive upstream.  
   - Ingredient planning now backtracks across candidate recipes (non-alt first) to avoid cyclic dead-ends when possible.  
   - Extractors: `_raw_*` keys via `getExtractorMachineOptionsFull`.
   - Quick Build plans are template-cached for all product+recipe(+miner) combinations and cloned with fresh ids per request.

3. **Plan ‚Üí `TreeNode`** ‚Üí `src/lib/plannerToTree.ts`  
   - Spine parent = deepest supplier; others ‚Üí `inputEdges` with real **`FlowNode.id`**.

4. **UI** ‚Üí `src/components/QuickBuildModal.tsx` (product + recipe + miner; no target rate).
   - Can be launched to either replace the active factory tree or create a brand-new factory tab named from the selected recipe.

5. **Wire + balance** ‚Üí `src/components/FlowChart.tsx` (`handleQuickBuildConfirm`, `autoBalanceAfterEdit`).
   - `FlowChart` primes planner templates on mount (idle callback) via `primeQuickBuildTemplates()`.

6. **Shared node types** ‚Üí `src/lib/flowChartModel.ts` (also used by `chartStorage`).

7. **Tests:** `src/lib/productionPlanner.test.ts` ‚Äî run `npm test`.

Do not reintroduce a separate ‚Äúlinear only‚Äù quick-build path unless restoring an explicit fallback; the planner should cover multi-input recipes.
